The Type 45 destroyer HMS Defender has been sent to the Middle East to join the international mission protecting shipping in the Strait of Hormuz, the Royal Navy announced on 24 August. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network “HMS Defender will ensure the continuous availability of a ship to reassure and accompany merchant vessels,” it said. The Royal Navy previously announced on 12 August that Defender was deploying to the Asia Pacific region, while the Type 23 frigate HMS Kent would relieve the Type 45 destroyer HMS Duncan in the Gulf. “Both Defender and Kent will now work alongside international partners as part of the newly-formed International Maritime Security Construct,” it said on 24 August.